cs.LO, cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.PL, cs.CL

This paper deals with logical characterizations of languages of data words, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several subfields of computer science. The use of monadic second-order logic and finite automata suggests that the paper could be classified under cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory). The mention of data structures and algorithms for recognizing data languages suggests that the paper could also be classified under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of algebraic objects and the mention of generic structures suggests that the paper could be classified under cs.PL (Programming Languages) and cs.CL (Computational Logic).
